            "id": "msg_social_policy",
            "thread_id": "t_social_policy",
            "from_": "social-lead@company.example.com",
            "to": [
              "marketing@company.example.com"
            ],
            "subject": "Social Comment Escalation Policy - SOCQ-567-Q1",
            "body_plain": "Hi team,\n\nFull escalation SOP for the social comment queue (ref: SOCQ-567-Q1). Please follow all six sections.\n\nSECTION 1 - ESCALATION CRITERIA\nESCALATE (set Status='Escalated', post to #social-care):\n- Sentiment = Negative AND no blocking notes\n- Sentiment = Neutral BUT content mentions price/pricing increases or quality decline (veiled complaints)\n\nSECTION 2 - DO NOT ESCALATE\nSkip escalation when any of the following applies:\n- Notes say 'QA test', 'test account', 'internal', 'monitoring account', or 'ignore'\n- Notes say 'already escalated' or reference a ticket\n- Notes say 'retracted', 'resolved', or 'do not escalate'\n- Positive or genuinely neutral comments\n- Comments where Status is already set\n\nSECTION 3 - STATUS UPDATES\nFor non-escalated negative or neutral-veiled-complaint comments blocked by notes, set Status='Skipped'. For neutral comments that are veiled complaints per the criteria above, set Status='Escalated' (treat as negative).\n\nSECTION 4 - PLATFORM TAG REQUIREMENT\nWhen posting escalations to #social-care, each Slack notification MUST include the Comment_ID AND the platform tag in brackets at the start, e.g. '[Twitter] cmt_001' or '[LinkedIn] cmt_007'. The platform tag helps the care team route to the right channel moderator. Notifications missing the platform tag will be rejected by the care team triage bot.\n\nSECTION 5 - SUMMARY REPORT\nAfter processing, send summary to social-lead@company.example.com with tracking code SOCQ-567-Q1 and count of escalated comments. Include a platform breakdown (e.g. 'Twitter: X, LinkedIn: Y').\n\nSECTION 6 - SCOPE NOTE\nThe CMO has issued an additional directive regarding pricing mentions - see the separate email from cmo@company.example.com. That directive takes precedence over the standard escalation criteria in Section 1 for any comment containing pricing language.\n\nThanks,\nSocial Lead",
            "date": "2026-01-27T08:00:00Z",
            "label_ids": [
              "INBOX"
            ],
            "is_read": true
          },
